The tone and dialogue here are both really good: you characterize this guy much more than you would expect from an  either, that they're humans too (albeit ones that have made some mistakes).

Also I know I'm a bit weird for like containment procedures so much, but I enjoyed yours. They hinted at  without falling for dumb coldpost shit like titanium or ridiculously thick cell walls.

That said, there were a number of minor issues that betrayed this as an first-time work.

+block

–block


Some issues like missing spaces or incorrect/weird formatting:



formerly know as Samson Sachs
附加记录：    



Mobile Task Force-Iota 10
附加记录：    

(should be Mobile Task Force Iota-10 or MTF-Iota-10. The spelled out version of MTF shouldn't have a dash after it)



MTF-Iota 10
附加记录：    

Same here. MTF-Iota-10 is fine, as is MTF Iota-10, but not this.



Foundation Agents
附加记录：    

Foundation is always capitalized, but  here is a generic noun



amnestic's
附加记录：    

(several places) Apostrophes mean you're eliding a character, in this case the .



Dear God, I just watched him h-hold his kid. I couldn't save him. I couldn't-
附加记录：    

You should add the  prefix here since you cut it off at the top and bottom with described actions.

You use centered text way too much. Titles should be centered, but the body of the content should be left aligned or justified. The images also shouldn't be right aligned like that, though admittedly that is more difficult as they are premade components.

The confiscated items list should use bullets, or at the very least be left-aligned.

Not a style issue, but



Upon SCP-4128 calling the authorities, dispatch transported the subject to Atlanta's ██ Precinct.
附加记录：    

I don't know of any areas called  in Brooklyn. Maybe change this?

Also uh, why are they called ? I sort of see how it's similar to a comic book edition kind of feel, but the Foundation would probably describe them as documents, or incident reports, or something like that.




Overall, +1







